18 SECTION 1.
19 (a) As used in this Act, the term:
20 (1) "Ad valorem taxes for educational purposes" means all ad valorem taxes for
21 educational purposes levied by, for, or on behalf of the Spalding County school district,
22 except for any ad valorem taxes to pay interest on and to retire county school district
23 bonded indebtedness.
24 (2) "Homestead" means homestead as defined and qualified in Code Section 48-5-40 of
25 the O.C.G.A., as amended, with the additional qualification that it shall include not more
26 than five contiguous acres of homestead property.
27 (3) "Income" means gross income from all sources determined pursuant to Chapter 7 of
28 Title 48 of the O.C.G.A., as amended, for state income tax purposes, except income shall
29 not include income received as retirement, survivor, or disability benefits under the
30 federal Social Security Act or under any other public or private retirement, disability, or
31 pension system, except such income which is in excess of the maximum amount
32 authorized to be paid to an individual and such individual's spouse under the federal
33 Social Security Act. Income from such sources in excess of such maximum amount shall
34 be included as income for the purposes of this Act.
35 (4) "Senior citizen" means a person who is 65 years of age or older on or before
36 January 1 of the year in which application for the exemption under subsection (b) of this
37 section is made.
38 (b) Each resident of the Spalding County school district who is a senior citizen is granted
39 an exemption on such person's homestead from Spalding County school district ad valorem
40 taxes for educational purposes in:
41 (1) The full amount of the assessed value of such homestead. The exemption under this
42 paragraph shall only be granted if such person's income, together with the income of the
43 spouse who also occupies and resides at such homestead, does not exceed $25,000.00 for
