45 amount shall remain subject to taxation.
46 (2) The amount of half of the assessed value of such homestead. The exemption under
47 this paragraph shall only be granted if such person's income, together with the income of
48 the spouse who also occupies and resides at such homestead, exceeds $25,000.00 and
49 does not exceed $53,000.00 for the immediately preceding year. The value of that
50 property in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
51 (3) The amount of 25 percent of the assessed value of such homestead. The exemption
52 under this subsection shall only be granted if such person's income, together with the
53 income of the spouse who also occupies and resides at such homestead, exceeds
54 $53,000.00 for the immediately preceding year. The value of that property in excess of
55 such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
56 (c) A person shall not receive the homestead exemption granted by subsection (b) of this
57 section unless such person or person's agent files an application with the tax commissioner
58 of Spalding County, giving such person's age, income, and such additional information
59 relative to receiving such exemption as will enable the tax commissioner of Spalding County
60 to make a determination regarding the initial and continuing eligibility of such person for
61 such exemption. The tax commissioner of Spalding County shall provide application forms
62 for this purpose.
63 (d) The exemption shall be claimed and returned as provided in Code Section 48-5-50.1 of
64 the O.C.G.A., as amended. The exemption shall be automatically renewed from year to year
65 so long as the person granted the homestead exemption under subsection (b) of this section
66 occupies the residence as a homestead. After such person has filed the proper application as
67 provided in subsection (c) of this section, it shall not be necessary to make application
68 thereafter for any year, and such exemption shall continue to be allowed to such person. It
69 shall be the duty of any such person granted the homestead exemption under subsection (b)
