103 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
104 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
105 such question are for approval of the Act, Section 1 of this Act shall become of full force and
106 effect on January 1, 2026. If the Act is not so approved or if the election is not conducted as
107 provided in this section, Section 1 of this Act shall not become effective, and this Act shall
108 be automatically repealed on the 365th calendar day following the election date provided for
109 in this section. The expense of such election shall be borne by Spalding County. It shall be
110 the election superintendent's duty to certify the result thereof to the Secretary of State. The
111 provisions of this section shall be mandatory upon the election superintendent and are not
112 intended as directory. If the election superintendent fails or refuses to comply with this
113 section, any elector of the Spalding County school district may apply for a writ of mandamus
114 to compel the election superintendent to perform his or her duties under this section. If the
115 court finds that the election superintendent has not complied with this section, the court shall
